com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core
Interface ConstraintLink

All Superinterfaces:
DeployLink, DeployModelObject
public interface ConstraintLink
extends DeployLink

A representation of the model object 'Logical Link'. Constraint links express a high-level binary constraint pattern between two entities.

The endpoints of constraint links can be any type of DeployModelObject. The semantics of a constraint link is determined by the child constraint of the link. Constraint links may be created in various ways. There is a UI tool to create constaints links with a predefined constraint, by using context menu for a pair of selected objects. Another way to be able to create a constraint link is for a constraint extension to declare a specialized link matcher in the com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.constraints extension point (using <linkMatcher/> element).

getTargetURI

java.lang.String getTargetURI()
Returns the unresolved URI of the logical link target.

Users should invoke getTarget() to obtain the resolved target. This method will typically used to determine if there was a resolution error when getTarget() returns null
